  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Assuming Schengen Access</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Cyprus is EU but NOT in the Schengen Area. Your Cyprus residence permit doesn't grant Schengen travel rights. You'll need separate visas/entries for Schengen countries based on your nationality.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Expecting GESY Coverage</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Digital Nomad Visa holders must use private insurance—you're not enrolled in GESY (public healthcare). Don't arrive expecting to use the public system.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Summer Heat</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Cyprus summers are extremely hot (35-40°C). If you're not used to intense heat, plan for air conditioning costs and limited outdoor activities mid-day June-September.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Understanding Non-Dom Rules</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Non-dom status is attractive but has specific requirements. You must have been non-resident in Cyprus for 17 of the past 20 years. Consult a tax advisor before relying on these benefits.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Forgetting Car Dependency</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Public transport in Cyprus is limited. Outside Nicosia, you'll likely need a car for comfortable living. Factor this into your budget and plans.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

